<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871113-0148 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:ISS International Chief,President Will Step Down</HL><DD> 11/13/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> ISI WNEWS </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   ISS International Service System Inc. said James N. Perry will step down as president and chief executive officer Feb. 29 but will remain vice chairman.    He will be succeeded by Henrik Slipsager, 32 years old, currently executive vice president and chief operating officer. He joined ISS in 1984 as chief financial officer.    In a statement, the company said Mr. Perry, 55, joined ISS &quot;with the express assignment to return the company to profitability and position it for growth.&quot; It added, &quot;This goal has been achieved and the designation of a new chief executive officer completes the assignment.&quot;    ISS provides cleaning, security, mechanical and other related maintenance services. </TEXT></DOC>